      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"5. PAX BOSTONIA was a winner (36.06) at this track two back but out of the placings last time when 7th at The Gardens. Form here at the trip sound including two wins. Has a strong record from box 5, including two wins. Better than last start and worth following up. 4. IT'S ALL BAD comes off an average effort last start when fifth at this track over 520m behind Towering Earl (30.09) in a Grade 5. Has the ability to give this a shake. 2. BANDIT BAY had been racing in honest fashion recording three placings in a row before finishing fourth (33.19) at Temora latest. Should be in this for a long way. 1. SIN CITY BANDIT is new to this trip but is worth considering.\",\"runners\":[5,4,2,1],\"exclusive\":false}",
